The paper discusses communication over the AWGN channel and focuses on improving the finite length performance of sparse superposition codes with approximate message passing (AMP) decoding. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Communications (cs.COMM), and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions optimizing power allocations and codebook parameters, which are related to Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
